ðŸ”— SQL JOIN Types Summary
Join Type	What It Does	Example Scenario
INNER JOIN	Returns only rows where there is a match in both tables	Customers with orders only
LEFT JOIN	Returns all rows from the left table + matched rows on right	All customers, even if they have no orders
RIGHT JOIN	Returns all rows from the right table + matched rows on left	All orders, even if they have no matching customer
FULL OUTER JOIN	Returns all rows from both tables, matched or not	All customers and all orders, including unmatched ones
